          Filigare
        </name>
            </rs>, June 23<lb/>
Journal 1819.<lb/>
I have resolved to keep a journal of the<lb/>
journey I am about to make. I have felt<lb/>
that through life I have lost many thoughts<lb/>
that were worth preserving, not only for my<lb/>
own amusement, but for the amusement of others<lb/>
I believe I have often made observations and<lb/>
combinations that were new, at least I never met<lb/>
with them in books, and the present state of<lb/>
society and of knowledge is different from<lb/>
any that ever existed. Man has made a<lb/>
wonderful progress in physical knowledge:<lb/>
there are many profound thinkers in every thing<lb/>
belonging to the progress of political improve-<lb/>
-ment; but the governors of the world are children<lb/>
compared with their servants. The useful acts<lb/>
have made a much greater progress than at<lb/>
any former period; and the imaginations of<lb/>
men subdued by the sense of utility, no<lb/>
longer kindles into poetry, or freezes in<lb/>
profound metaphysics. A few scintillations<lb/>
shine in the gloom; but the public consider<lb/>
            <lb/>
            <pb xmlns:conf="https://www.lancaster.ac.uk/library/ns/digital-library/config/1.0"
                n="6"
                xml:id="pb-6"
                facs="#i6"/>
            <lb/>
them as dangerous, and not as likely to<lb/>
kindle into a permanent and useful <del xmlns:conf="https://www.lancaster.ac.uk/library/ns/digital-library/config/1.0"
                 rend="strikethrough">system</del>
            <add xmlns:conf="https://www.lancaster.ac.uk/library/ns/digital-library/config/1.0">fire</add>,<lb/>
but rather as leading to a dangerous conflagration<lb/>
and the persons who possess them as incendiaries<lb/>
A. person viewing nature and society without<lb/>
prejudice may at this moment amuse himself<lb/>
and perhaps instruct others. I left the <rs xmlns:conf="https://www.lancaster.ac.uk/library/ns/digital-library/config/1.0"
                xml:id="ttag2"
                ref="#place_952"
                type="place">
               <name xml:id="tag2" type="place">
          baths<lb/>of Lucca
        </name>
            </rs>
