materials carried down by rivers, then<lb/>
they glitter and are found: then their<lb/>
immortality is known and they are<lb/>
employed to ornament the diadems of<lb/>
Emperors and the Sceptres of Kings: they<lb/>
press under them the brows of majesty.<lb/>
They lie too deep to be readily found.<lb/>
