          Palais Royale
        </name>
            </rs>. Every one there lives for<lb/>
himself: vice is exhibited in all <hi xmlns:conf="https://www.lancaster.ac.uk/library/ns/digital-library/config/1.0"
                rend="underline">its</hi>
            <lb/>
magnificence; and the luxurious repose<lb/>
of the sensualist, is only diversified by the<lb/>
hopes and fears of the gambler. I can<lb/>
            <lb/>
            <pb xmlns:conf="https://www.lancaster.ac.uk/library/ns/digital-library/config/1.0"
                n="150"
                xml:id="pb-150"
                facs="#i150"/>
            <lb/>
hardly imagine any thing more fatal<lb/>
to the exquisite sensibility, <del xmlns:conf="https://www.lancaster.ac.uk/library/ns/digital-library/config/1.0"
