is moved by every breeze; shoots forth<lb/>
its leaves vigorously when favoured by<lb/>
dew &amp; sunshine: but is often severely<lb/>
injured if not destroyed by frosts.<lb/>
In the mature tree as the heartwood<lb/>
is covered by many coatings of sapwood<lb/>
it becomes compressed &amp; harder: but<lb/>
though it loses its vitality, it contributes<lb/>
to the strength of the vegetable.<lb/>
